This paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category as it proposes a new framework for on-policy reinforcement learning using entropy regularization. It also uses the soft gradient policy theorem, which is a common technique in machine learning. Additionally, the paper presents experimental results on continuous control benchmark tasks, which are often used in machine learning research. 

The paper could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category as it proposes a new algorithm for reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of AI. 

The Robotics (cs.RO) category is also a likely fit as the paper discusses the application of the proposed algorithm to control tasks in robotics. 

The Systems and Control (cs.SY) category is another possibility as the paper deals with control problems and proposes a new algorithm for solving them. 

Finally, the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category is a less likely fit, but still possible as the paper deals with continuous control tasks, which could involve visual inputs.
